-- Saudi Arabian Mining to Start Exporting Phosphate in December, Awsat Says
-- Mourad Haroutunian
-- 2010-08-01T06:01:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-01/saudi-arabian-mining-to-start-exporting-phosphate-in-december-awsat-says.html

          
          
             Saudi Arabian Mining Co. , the state-
controlled metals producer known as Maâ€™aden, will in December
start exporting diammonium phosphate from its al-Jalamid site,
 Asharq al-Awsat  reported, citing Chief Executive Officer
 Abdullah al-Dabbagh .  
 The facility is expected to produce 3 million tons of
granular diammonium phosphate, 440,000 tons of liquefied
ammonia, and 200,000 tons of fertilizer-grade phosphoric acid
per year, the newspaper reported.  
